  {
    "page": 5,
    "block_id": "p09_v_szz_automatic_identification_version_ranges_2022:block:005:035",
    "block_type": "text",
    "text": "To investigate the effectiveness of the SZZ algorithms, we need a\nground truth linking vulnerabilities and the true inducing commits.\nHowever, to the best of our knowledge, no such ground truth ex-\nists. Nguyen et al. manually verified the results generated by their\napproach for 80 vulnerabilities from two projects, but they did not\nmake the dataset public [38]. Thus, in this section, we aim to build a\nground truth linking vulnerabilities and their corresponding induc-\ning commits. We first select two datasets with vulnerability-fixing\ncommits. Then, we annotate the inducing commits for vulnerabili-\nties by following the model proposed by Rodríguez-Pérez et al. [44],\nand manually verify the vulnerable versions based on the anno-\ntated inducing commits. Finally, we present the results of manual\nannotation.\n",
    "bbox": [
      317.6860046386719,
      425.292236328125,
      559.7047119140625,
      569.1902465820312
    ],
    "reading_order": 35,
    "column_guess": null,
    "confidence": "medium"
  },
