  {
    "page": 5,
    "block_id": "p09_v_szz_automatic_identification_version_ranges_2022:block:005:037",
    "block_type": "text",
    "text": "To investigate whether our proposed approach can detect induc-\ning commits for vulnerabilities and refine vulnerable versions ef-\nfectively, we select two datasets of vulnerability-fixing commits\ncontaining projects written in two programming languages, i.e.,\nC/C++ [30] and Java [43], respectively. Table 1 presents the statis-\ntics of the vulnerabilities and the corresponding fixing commits\nin the two datasets. In this table, #Vul and #VFC are the number\nof the vulnerabilities and the fixing commits, respectively. Notice\nthat some vulnerabilities have multiple fixing commits. We also\ncount the vulnerability fixing commits that have no deleted lines\n",
    "bbox": [
